$Id$

List of examples in examples-share-doc
======================================
*.sh, *.bat: Linux/Windows scripts from the GMT documentation tree (GMT_SHAREDIR/doc/examples)
*.f90: equivalent Fortran codes (gmt.f90 required)

Compilation
- by call to 'make' or by a command similar to 'f90 gmt.f90 example.f90 -Lpath_to_gmt_lib -lgmt'
- tested with GNU, Intel, PGI and g95, Linux and Windows
- alternative source files example_??b.f90: + operator overloaded for strings
- ex16: PostScript output by API calls errorneous (PS output by shell scripts ok)

Notes
-----
- the simplest way preferred, i.e., subroutines with optional arguments without error checking
- calls to ps2raster added to original scripts
- redirection shell operators should be changed to equivalent GMT options:
  example: *.sh  ... > file.ps ; >> file.ps
           *.f90 ... ->file.ps ; ->>file.ps

